System_processes.name: System processes
System_processes.content:
# This page
Will show the different processes
that are scheduled in the system

Each will contain the description
of the task, where is is run
when it is run and the specific 
name of the procedure that is run


# Session Cleanup
- Run: every 5 minutes
- Description: cleans up the old
	unused sessions from the DB
- Procedure: ` exec Staff.db.Session_Cleanup`

# Send Payslips
- Run: 7am on the last friday 
	of the month
- Description: calculates the
	payslips from the timesheets
    and sends out the produced
    reports to the staff's email
- Procedure: ` exec Staff.db.Send_Payslips `

Tables.name: Tables
Tables.content:
# Schema: App

- Staff:
	FirstName [VARCHAR]
    LastName [VARCHAR]
    StaffID [INT] [PRIMARY]
    Wage [MONEY]

- Role:
	Name [VARCHAR]
    RoleID [INT] [PRIMARY]
    Created [DATETIME]
    
- StaffRole:
	StaffID [INT] FK[Staff]
    RoleID [INT] FK[Role]
    Started [DATETIME]
    Finished [DATETIME]

Procedures.name: Procedures

Views.name: Views
Views.content:
# Views

## StaffRole
- Description: contains a
	composite view of both staff
    and their roles
- Used by: ProduceRota[View]
- Last updated: 2015-03-34

## TimesheetByDivision
- Description: contains an
	aggregate view of timesheet
    information by division

## StaffHistory
- Description: contains a history
	of old roles that a member of
    staff has
- Used by: Produce

# RroduceRota
- Description: contains available
	slots and a mapping of what 
    member of staff can use them

to.

# New developments
There are some new developments
planned

Phase_overview.name: Phase overview
Phase_overview.content:
# Phase details

A Set of tables to allow automatic
timesheet generation has been 
added, each employee has a swipe 
card and there are two readers IN
/ OUT.

# New Tables
-	SwipeCard
  CardID [INT] [PRIMARY]
  
-	CardReader
  ReaderID [INT] [PRIMARY]
  IN [BIT]
  
-	SwipeLog
  CardID [INT]
  ReaderID [INT]
  LogTime [DATETIME]

Query.name: Query
Query.content:
declare @log table (
  LogID int identity(1,1) primary key,
  Created datetime default (getdate()) not null,
  EmployeeID int not null,
  ino int default (0) not null
);

insert into @log (EmployeeID,ino)
values 
(1,1),
(1,0),
(2,1),
(3,1),
(2,0),
(3,0),
(1,1),
(1,1);

select * from @log;

New_Query.name: New Query
New_Query.content:
declare @log table (
  LogID int identity(1,1) primary key,
  Created datetime default (getdate()) not null,
  EmployeeID int not null,
  ino int default (0) not null
);

insert into @log (EmployeeID,ino)
values 
(1,1),
(1,0),
(2,1),
(3,1),
(2,0),
(3,0);

select 
  EmployeeID, 
  ino, 
  count(1) as [Count]
from @log
group by EmployeeID, ino;
